-- SABMiller: will seek talks with Foster's board to secure offer
-- 
-- Mon Jun 20, 2011 10:22pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/21/us-fosters-sab-talks-idUSTRE75K02820110621

 

 SYDNEY, Jun  (Reuters) - Global brewer SABMiller ( SAB.L ) says it will continue to seek engagement with the board of Foster's Group FGL.AX in a bid to secure an agreed takeover offer. 

 SABMiller said in a statement released in Sydney it would finance a bid from existing resources and new debt facilities. Foster's earlier said it had rejected a $10 billion offer from SABMiller. (Reporting by  Michael Smith ; Editing by  Ed Davies )